Michael Vaughan cited Virat Kohli's recent life changes, including his prioritization of family, including missing the five-Test series between India and England for the birth of his son, Akaay.
title: Vaughan feels these things may take Kohli away from cricket

description: The mother of a 17-year-old boy in Pune seeks police protection after a fake video circulates online, showing him boasting about a fatal car crash. The teenager, allegedly driving a Porsche and causing the accident, is in detention.
title: 'Protect my son': Mother of teen in Pune car crash to cops

description: The Arab League called for UN peacemakers in Gaza and West Bank. The UN chief highlighted the limitations of peacekeeping in Israeli occupied territories, citing the lack of prerequisites to stop the war.
title: Don't expect UN peacekeepers to stop wars: Chief

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in red but within minutes reversed losses to trade in green.
title: BSE Sensex near 75,500 level; Nifty50 shy of 23,000

description: At least 100 people are feared dead in Kaokalam, Papua New Guinea's Enga province after a devastating landslide struck Enga province. Updates about recovery efforts are yet to be confirmed as villagers scramble to recover bodies and rescue the trapped. Various footages circulating on various social media platforms are depicting the aftermath of the disaster.
title: At least 100 feared dead after landslide strikes Papua New Guinea

description: The Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) is processing a request by the Karnataka government to cancel the diplomatic passport of Prajwal Revanna, the suspended Janata Dal (Secular) MP who is accused of sexual abuse of several women and is believed to be in Germany now. Official sources said the MEA has begun the process to revoke Prajwal's passport after receiving a letter from the Karnataka government.
title: Will Prajwal Revanna return to India after Gowda's warning?

description: USCIS's sharp rise in US H-1B visa fees poses challenges for Indian IT service providers, impacting business operations. The fee hikes, including a 2050% increase in registration fee and a $600 asylum fee, may force companies to exit the visa process.
title: Will Indian IT companies be forced to exit H1-B visa program?

description: After weeks of pro-Palestine rallies by students at US campuses, hundreds of students wearing graduation gowns walked out of Harvard's commencement ceremony on Thursday, chanting "free, free Palestine".
title: 'Free Palestine' chants at Harvard commencement ceremony

description: A bipartisan group of US senators has urged Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau to formulate a plan to meet Nato's defense spending commitment of 2% of GDP. Democratic Senator Jeanne Shaheen, Republican Senator Thom Tillis, and 21 other senators signed a letter to Trudeau, emphasizing the importance of reaching the target agreed upon in 2006 and reaffirmed in 2023.
title: US senators tell Trudeau to meet Nato defense spending pledge

description: A man in Budaun received life imprisonment for attacking his pregnant wife to determine the baby's gender. The incident occurred in the Civil Lines area on September 19, 2020. The accused was convinced by a village priest that his wife, Anita Devi, was expecting another girl. The court found him guilty of causing miscarriage without the woman's consent.
title: UP man slits open wife’s womb to check baby's gender

description: In a thrilling match in Texas, Ali Khan became a hero for the USA as they clinched a crucial victory by six runs against Bangladesh, securing a 2-0 lead in the series. His three-wicket haul stalled Bangladesh's chase, and Saurabh Netravalkar contributed significantly. This victory marked the USA's first series win against a top-ten T20I team.
title: Khan, Patel propel US to historic T20 victory over Bangladesh

description: Medical staff at a government hospital in Molakalmuru, Chitradurga district, Karnataka, facing challenges due to persistent power outages, resorting to torches and candles. Video on social media shows the dire situation. Hospital management under fire for non-functional backup generator.
title: On cam: Doctors perform operation using mobile flashlight

description: The West Bengal CID detained a man for alleged involvement in the murder of Bangladesh MP Anwarul Azim Anar. Police believe the MP was lured to a New Town flat by a woman and killed by contract killers. The detained individual, residing near the Bangladesh border, had contact with a main suspect in the case.
title: Cops suspect Bangladesh MP 'honey-trapped' before 'murder'

title: Sunrisers Hyderabad eye redemption against resurgent RR

description: National Brother's Day is celebrated on May 24 to honor the importance of having brothers in our lives, appreciating their presence, and expressing gratitude and love for them through messages and quotes.
title: National Brothers Day 2024: Top 50 wishes messages & quotes

description: UP police traced a bomb hoax email to a Class 8 girl from Thane, Maharashtra, linked to the May 10 hoax at Birla Open Mind International School in Sushant Golf City. The girl had no ulterior motive and was not affiliated with the school. ATS officials revealed the girl used the chat app 'Discord' for the prank among friends.
title: Class 8 Thane girl tied to UP bomb hoax, but she's innocent: Cops

description: Ashwin's crucial role for Royals in Chepauk qualifier vs SRH, battling injury, facing Kolkata Knight Riders, with Travis Head, Abhishek Sharma, Heinrich Klaasen, Yuzvendra Chahal, CSK, and challenging Virat Kohli & Co. Ashwin had an indifferent start to the IPL, but he has slowly come into his own at the back-end of the tournament. In 14 games, he has taken 9 wickets at an economy rate of 8.31, which is probably not his best.
title: A 'tale of two IPLs' for Ravichandran Ashwin

description: On Friday, China began the second day of military drills surrounding Taiwan to test the "capability of joint seizure of power, joint strikes, and control of key territories," according to People's Liberation Army spokesperson Li Xi. In response, Taiwan has mobilized its sea, air, and ground forces in response to the drills.​​​​​​
title: 'Seizure of power': China starts 2nd day of military drills around Taiwan

description: Virat Kohli reflects on RCB's loss to Rajasthan Royals in the IPL playoffs, expressing pride in the team's turnaround despite dashed title hopes. ​​The agonizing wait for a maiden IPL trophy has now stretched to 17 years. His peers, MS Dhoni and Rohit Sharma, in contrast, have lifted the cup five times each.
title: For Virat Kohli, perfection is a lonely pursuit

description: Four people died and 21 were injured after a restaurant roof collapsed in Mallorca, Spain, with victims of various nationalities. The victims were taken to different hospitals with seven being "very serious" and nine suffering "serious" injuries, according to a post by the emergency services on X. Spain PM Pedro Sanchez expressed his condolences to the family of the deceased.
title: At least four dead, 21 injured in Spain restaurant roof collapse
